{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"stab-bunch-foyer","description":"## What\n\n`transition <id> open in_progress` currently bypasses the plan-review claim gate that `claim` enforces. Starting work via a plain transition should apply the SAME validation (require a certified plan-review attestation, or `--force` with an audit note). The gate logic, today living in `src/rebar/_commands/claim.py::_plan_review_precheck`, must be consolidated into a single shared method that both the claim path and the transition path call — so the two cannot drift.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The plan-review gate validation lives in ONE method (consolidated out of `claim.py` into a shared home, e.g. `src/rebar/_commands/gates.py`).\n- [ ] `claim_compute` calls the consolidated method (behavior unchanged; existing claim-gate tests still pass).\n- [ ] `transition_compute` calls the consolidated method when transitioning `open -> in_progress`, blocking (fail-closed) on a missing/stale attestation when the gate is enabled, and exempting bug/session_log.\n- [ ] `--force` (with audit comment) bypasses the gate on the transition path, mirroring claim.\n- [ ] New tests cover the transition open->in_progress gate (blocked / force-bypass / bug-exempt / earned-attestation-succeeds).","id":"65e3-1fc6-5f3b-4c67","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Apply plan-review gate to open->in_progress transition; consolidate claim/transition gate logic"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782519129182322001,"uuid":"2350c658-556c-444a-b190-885a35ead47a"}